LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 125
BY JUDICIARY, RULES AND ADMINISTRATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO RIOTS; AMENDING SECTION 18-6402, IDAHO CODE, TO PROVIDE A
3 PENALTY AND TO MAKE TECHNICAL CORRECTIONS; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY
4 AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 SECTION 1. That Section 18-6402, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
7 amended to read as follows:
8 18-6402. RIOT -- FELONY -- MISDEMEANOR -- PUNISHMENT. (1) A riot is a
9 felony if:
10 (a) It occurs on or about the state penitentiary, a county or city
11 jail, or any other penal facility in this state, or it involves the tak-
12 ing of one (1) or more hostages. Violation of the provisions of this
13 subsection paragraph is punishable by imprisonment in the state peni-
14 tentiary for not less than five (5) years, no nor more than twenty (20)
15 years, or a fine not to exceed twenty-five thousand dollars ($25,000),
16 or both such fine and imprisonment.;
17 (b) The destruction or damage to public or private property exceeds
18 five hundred dollars ($500). Violation of the provisions of this
19 subsection paragraph is punishable by imprisonment in the state pen-
20 itentiary for not more than five (5) years or a fine not to exceed ten
21 thousand dollars ($10,000), or both such fine and imprisonment.; or
22 (c) It results in physical injury to any person. Violation of the pro-
23 visions of this paragraph is punishable by imprisonment in the state
24 penitentiary for not more than five (5) years or a fine not to exceed ten
25 thousand dollars ($10,000), or both such fine and imprisonment.
26 (2) A riot is a misdemeanor in all other circumstances punishable by im-
27 prisonment in the city or county jail for not more than one (1) year and a fine
28 not to exceed five thousand dollars ($5,000).
29 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
30 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
31 July 1, 2025.

